<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-12-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-12-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="154" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d154">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">Roosevelt Papers: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">Prime Minister <persName corresp="#p_CWS1" type="from">Churchill</persName> to President <persName corresp="#p_RFD1" type="to">Roosevelt</persName>
                                </hi><note n="1" xml:id="d154fn1">Channel of transmission not
                                    indicated on copy.</note>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Excerpt]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-12-16">16 December 1944</date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>853. I thank you cordially for your telegram Number 674 about Poland.
                                I trust you will carry out your proposal to send a message to
                                    <persName corresp="#p_S16">Stalin</persName> suggesting that he
                                postpone any positive action on the Polish <pb facs="0301" n="217" xml:id="pg_217"/> question until the three of us can get
                                together. This suggestion is most valuable and also I feel extremely
                                urgent. Would it be possible for you to do this today, as I
                                apprehend <persName corresp="#p_S16">Stalin</persName> may make some
                                move recognizing the Lublin Committee as the government of
                                Poland.</p>
                            <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Prime</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>